{"questionId":"22246","questionHtml":"<div class=\"qb-parent-stem\"><p>Consider the expression&nbsp;<math xmlns=\"http://www.w3.org/1998/Math/MathML\"><mfrac><mn>1</mn><msqrt><mn>1</mn><mo>+</mo><mi>a</mi><mi>x</mi></msqrt></mfrac><mo>-</mo><msqrt><mn>1</mn><mo>-</mo><mi>x</mi></msqrt></math>&nbsp;where&nbsp;<math xmlns=\"http://www.w3.org/1998/Math/MathML\"><mi>a</mi><mo>∈</mo><mi mathvariant=\"normal\">ℚ</mi><mo>,</mo><mo>&nbsp;</mo><mi>a</mi><mo>≠</mo><mn>0</mn></math>.</p>\n<p>The binomial expansion of this expression, in ascending powers of&nbsp;<math xmlns=\"http://www.w3.org/1998/Math/MathML\"><mi>x</mi></math>, as far as the term in <math xmlns=\"http://www.w3.org/1998/Math/MathML\"><msup><mi>x</mi><mn>2</mn></msup></math>&nbsp;is <math xmlns=\"http://www.w3.org/1998/Math/MathML\"><mn>4</mn><mi>b</mi><mi>x</mi><mo>+</mo><mi>b</mi><msup><mi>x</mi><mn>2</mn></msup></math>, where&nbsp;<math xmlns=\"http://www.w3.org/1998/Math/MathML\"><mi>b</mi><mo>∈</mo><mi mathvariant=\"normal\">ℚ</mi></math>.</p></div>\n<div class=\"qb-leaf-prompt\"><p>State the restriction which must be placed on <math xmlns=\"http://www.w3.org/1998/Math/MathML\"><mi>x</mi></math> for this expansion to be valid.</p></div>","markschemeHtml":"<p><math xmlns=\"http://www.w3.org/1998/Math/MathML\"><mfenced open=\"|\" close=\"|\"><mi>x</mi></mfenced><mo>&lt;</mo><mn>1</mn></math> &nbsp; &nbsp; &nbsp; &nbsp; &nbsp; &nbsp; &nbsp;<em><strong>A1</strong></em></p>\n<p>&nbsp;</p>\n<p><em><strong>[1</strong></em><em><strong>&nbsp;mark]</strong></em></p>","meta":{"questionId":"22246","referenceCode":"21N.1.AHL.TZ0.9b","subjectId":"50-dp-mathematics-analysis-and-approaches","title":"State the restriction which must be placed on x for this expansion to be valid.","paper":"1","level":"HL","questionNumber":"b","marksAvailable":"[Maximum mark: 1]","breadcrumbLabels":["Topic 1—Number and algebra","Topic 5 —Calculus","Topic 5 —Calculus","AHL 5.19—Maclaurin series","Topic 1—Number and algebra","AHL 1.10—Perms a